fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-010",
  description: "Implement type-unification helpers as anthill rules so type_of(?env, ?occ, ?type) rules (WI-011) can reason about types declaratively. Three relations to define: (a) subtype(?sub, ?sup) / assignable(?from, ?to) covering primitive subtyping and structural compatibility; (b) resolve_sort_alias(?sort, ?canonical) walking SortAlias facts; (c) unify_type(?a, ?b) orchestrating structural match + alias resolution + subtyping. The Rust unify_types (typing.rs:1131) stays as the operational fast path used by type_check. Note: Type values are already plain Term::Fn and unify structurally via SLD — the original 'Sort is opaque' framing was inaccurate. The unused sort_as_term/term_as_sort/can_be_sort stubs in reflect.anthill:136-140 should be removed as cleanup.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Open)

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-011",
  description: "Typing as rules: express the typing pass as anthill rules (not just operations) using type_of(?env, ?occ, ?type) 3-arg relation. TypingEnv as data sort with constructors (empty, bind). Requires: (1) Sort in unifications (WI-010), (2) forward chaining or materialization to persist derived TypeOf facts, (3) tabling/memoization for recursive derivations. See Proposal 022 and 011 discussion. CLOSED 2026-04-23 (decision verified, scope abandoned): the original premises are addressed without needing the Horn-rules lift. (a) Sort participation in unification is implemented — types are plain Term::Fn and unify structurally via SLD; rust unify_types (typing.rs:1131) is the operational helper. (b) Typing logic is already expressed in anthill code via typing_pass_spec.anthill (operations-form spec, not Horn-rule form, but serving the same documentation/specification purpose). (c) Forward chaining and tabling infrastructure is significant work with no current consumer — better added when a real use case appears. Followup: WI-079 covers parity-testing between the operations-form spec and the Rust implementation. Do not reopen without a concrete use case for the Horn-rules form specifically.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: ["WI-010"],
  status: Verified(at: "2026-04-23T00:00:00Z"))
