fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-047",
  description: "026.1 Q3: execute(LogicalQuery) + reflect.KB eval builtins. Core: kb.execute_logical_query(q: &Value) -> SearchStream and lower_query(&Value) -> Vec<TermId> over LogicalQuery constructors in reflect.anthill (pattern_query, conjunction, guarded, projected, limited, single-goal negation; disjunction/multi-goal negation/quantifiers deferred per WI-075/WI-076/WI-048). alloc_from_value recursively promotes Value → TermId via TermStore::alloc — the sole input-boundary hash-cons site. Wired as builtin backing anthill.reflect.KB.execute. Plus 23 additional reflect builtins registered via anthill-stl/src/reflect/builtins.rs::register_reflect_builtins: KB.{sort_template, sorts, operations, constructors, fields, rules, descriptions, reify, reflect, nonvar, ground}; namespace ops {qualified_name, short_name, lookup_symbol, scope, kind, sort_as_term, term_as_sort, can_be_sort, field_access, resolve_sort_instantiation_param, Substitution.apply, Substitution.compose}. New first-class Value::Substitution(SubstHandle) variant + SubstArena (eval/subst_arena.rs); LogicalStream.splitFirst now yields Value::Substitution. Supporting kernel additions: Interpreter::call short-circuits to builtins; KnowledgeBase::{kind_of, scope_of}; SymbolTable::iter_defs; register_if_present + expect_args exported from anthill-core::eval::builtins. Acceptance: 16/16 anthill-stl tests + 606/606 workspace tests pass. Delivered 2026-04-23. See docs/status/wi-047.md. Follow-ups: WI-075 (disjunction), WI-076 (multi-goal negation), WI-048 (quantifiers/aggregations); reflect.not(query) deferred to a new WI; KB.assert/add_guard (proposal 023), occurrence ops (proposal 022), instantiation_query (design) split out.",
