fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-113",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase α.3 — Tactic interface returns ProofWitness. Refactor dispatch_z3, dispatch_derivation, dispatch_ranking, dispatch_induction in rustland/anthill-cli/src/prove.rs to return Result<ProofWitness, Error> instead of Verdict. CLI verdict-printing layer wraps the witness for user output. Witness construction per tactic kind: dispatch_z3 produces SmtDischarge with backend/logic/document_hash/verdict/core; meta-tactics produce MetaCompose carrying their sub-tactics' witnesses; derivation produces SldDerivation with tree_hash. Existing verdict-style behavior is preserved — the witness is just additional structure carried alongside. See docs/proposals/030-theorem-registry.md phase α.3.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: ["WI-112"],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-04-28T10:32:13Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-114",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase α.4 — implement compute_state_hash(visited_rules, kb) for ProofRecord. Per phase α.4 of docs/proposals/030-theorem-registry.md: produces canonical hash of the kb-state slice a discharge depended on (every visited rule's IR + every referenced fact's content). Reuses WI-096's build_key infrastructure (rustland/anthill-smt-gen/src/cache/key.rs walk_visited + fact_dep_hash_from), but produces a per-ProofRecord state hash separate from the SMT-document cache key. Integration: dispatch_outcome path in prove.rs passes visited rule QNs through to a new helper; result populates ProofRecord.state_hash on Discharged outcomes. The hash invalidates: any visited rule's body changes, any referenced fact's content changes.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
