fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-116",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase α.6 — auto-register requires clauses as ProofRecords with ScopeAxiom witness. Per phase α.6 of docs/proposals/030-theorem-registry.md: at sort/operation load time, for each 'requires <SE>' clause inside scope S, the loader emits a synthetic ProofRecord fact with: rule = '<S-qn>.requires.<SE-flat>'; strategy = ProofStrategyOpen; body = ProofBodyNone; result = Discharged; witness = ScopeAxiom(scope_kind: 'sort' | 'operation', scope_qn: <S-qn>, aspect: 'requires.<SE-flat>'); state_hash = canonical hash of S's declaration; dependencies = []; using = []; parametric_context = derived from enclosing abstract sorts (empty for non-parametric). Sort-Expr flattening: 'Eq[T]' → 'Eq_T', 'Foo[A, B]' → 'Foo_A_B', etc. Idempotent — re-loading the same source produces the same ProofRecord QN. Acceptance: cargo-test passes; new test verifies a sort with a requires clause gets a Discharged ProofRecord with the expected witness shape.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-04-28T11:37:49Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-117",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase α.7 — auto-register induction principles as ScopeAxiom witnesses. Per phase α.7 of docs/proposals/030-theorem-registry.md: at sort load time, for each inductive sort (enum / inductive ADT) and supported primitive (Int, BigInt, ...), the loader emits a synthetic ProofRecord with: rule = '<sort-qn>.induction'; strategy = ProofStrategyOpen; body = ProofBodyNone; result = Pending; witness = ScopeAxiom(scope_kind: 'sort', scope_qn: <sort-qn>, aspect: 'induction'); state_hash = 'scope-axiom'; parametric_context derived from sort's abstract parameters (empty for monomorphic). Detection: walk SortInfo facts; for each sort with multiple entity-constructors (enum), or with self-referential constructor args (inductive ADT), or matching the primitives whitelist, register the principle. Idempotent. Acceptance: cargo-test passes; new test verifies an enum gets a single induction ProofRecord with the expected witness.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-04-28T11:46:19Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-118",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase α.8 — Specialization witness composition on provides discharge. DEFERRED: depends on the 'provides' discharge mechanism being operational, but load_provides_clause in rustland/anthill-core/src/kb/load.rs:4096 is a stub today. The compose operation needs: (1) a working 'provides A[T = X]' source-level discharge that fires at load; (2) lookup of A's auto-registered ScopeAxiom records (α.6); (3) emission of Specialization { parametric: A.requires.<SE>, substitution: [(T, X)], instances: [X.requires.<SE>] } per A's requires-clause. Spec satisfaction is currently expressed via 'fact Eq[T = Int]' style facts but those don't carry the parametric→specialized binding the kernel needs. Two follow-on WIs: (a) implement provides-discharge KB facts (SortProvidesInfo or analog) and load_provides_clause; (b) phase α.8 compose pass walking SortProvidesInfo + emitting Specialization records. Both phases β.5 (Specialization checking) and γ (using consults registry) are independent and can land before α.8. Acceptance: cargo-test passes; this WI is itself a NoOp stub register_specialization_witnesses() in load.rs that documents the deferral and is plumbed into load_phase for future expansion.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-04-28T11:50:16Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-119",
  description: "BRAINSTORM ACTIVITY (proposal 030 phase α.8 design pivot): do we need 'provides' clause at all? Insight: a sort X 'provides' spec S at substitution σ iff every requires-clause lemma of S has a kernel-checked ProofRecord at σ. That's a derived predicate, not a primitive declaration. Implications: (1) no new SortProvidesInfo schema needed — the relation lives in the ProofRecord registry already; (2) source-level 'provides A[T = X]' clause becomes optional, serving as documentation/intent marker only — actual discharge happens via concrete ProofRecords on the requires-clause lemmas; (3) load_provides_clause (currently stub) repurposed as a CHECK — does the user's claimed 'provides' have the supporting proofs? Error if not. Open questions: (a) does this mean parametric_context derivation in α.7's induction records gets simpler too? (b) for polymorphic specs like List[T] requires Eq[T], does the auto-derivation interact with the parametric_context field correctly? (c) what about specs whose requires-clauses themselves contain abstract references — do we need transitive closure? Decide before resuming WI-118 (Specialization composition). Acceptance: design notes captured here; document outcome in proposal 030 §α.8 or a §α.8.1 addendum.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("review")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-04-28T12:04:24Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-120",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase α.8 (re-scoped): implement Specialization composition by deriving 'provides' from requires-clause ProofRecords. After WI-119 brainstorm settles the design, walk: for each parametric spec S with auto-registered <S-qn>.requires.<SE> records, and each concrete sort X, check whether X has Discharged ProofRecords for each of S's requires-laws under substitution [T = X]. If yes, emit Specialization{ parametric: <S-qn>.requires.<SE>, substitution: [(T, X)], instances: [<X-qn>.<...>] } ProofRecords. Repurposes load_provides_clause as a check: the user's source-level 'provides A[T = X]' must have supporting proofs (error if not). Replaces the stub register_specialization_witnesses landed in WI-118.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: ["WI-119"],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-04-28T12:13:40Z"))

fact Feedback(content: "DECISION (2026-04-28): Variant 3 chosen. Source-level 'provides A[T = X]' declares intent → kernel verifies each requires-clause has a Discharged ProofRecord at substitution → emits SortProvidesInfo fact + Specialization ProofRecords for each requires-law. Rationale: (a) intent vs coincidence distinguishable; (b) load-time errors when proofs missing; (c) bounded O(provides-clauses) vs O(specs × sorts); (d) existing load_provides_clause stub fits cleanly; (e) phase β.5 Specialization checking doesn't need substituted rule bodies (Variant 2 conflates declaration with materialization). Optional Variant-1 nudge layer: after explicit Variant-3 discharge, walk for (Spec, Sort) pairs with all requires-laws proven but no explicit provides clause; emit non-blocking CLI suggestion. Open questions still TBD during implementation: polymorphic case (List[T] provides Foldable[T]), transitive provides for nested requires, parametric_context interaction with α.7.", at: "2026-04-28T12:04:15Z", workitem: "WI-119", author: "claude")
fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-121",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase β.1 — SmtDischarge witness checking. Per phase β.1 of docs/proposals/030-theorem-registry.md: re-run the cached SMT-LIB document via the named backend, verify verdict matches what the witness records. Implementation: new check_smt_discharge_witness(witness, blob_dir, solver_path) -> Result<(), CheckError>. Loads the SMT-LIB document blob via cache::load_blob(blob_dir, document_hash), invokes the named solver (z3 today; cvc5 in a follow-up), parses the verdict, compares to witness.verdict. Errors: missing blob (BlobMissing), verdict mismatch (VerdictMismatch{recorded, observed}), solver unavailable (SolverUnavailable). The check runs read-only (no caching). Slot in anthill-cli/src/check.rs (creating the file) — surfaces via the existing run_check stub at main.rs:1082. Acceptance: cargo-test passes; new test verifies a Discharged ProofRecord with SmtDischarge witness checks ok via blob round-trip.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-04-28T12:20:34Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-122",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase β.4 — ScopeAxiom witness checking. Per phase β.4 of docs/proposals/030-theorem-registry.md: re-read the named scope's declaration and dispatch on aspect. For aspect='requires.<SE-flat>': verify the requires <SE> clause is present in the scope (walk SortRequiresInfo facts for scope_qn, check at least one matches the SE-flat signature). For aspect='induction': verify the named sort exists and is inductively defined (SortInfo.kind = enum, or has constructors). On success, transition the ProofRecord's outcome to Pass. On failure (declaration missing, clause edited away, kind changed), Failed with a clear message. Acceptance: cargo-test passes; new tests verify (a) a sort with requires Eq[T] makes its ScopeAxiom requires record check Pass; (b) an enum sort makes its induction record check Pass; (c) a sort whose declaration is removed or whose kind changes makes the corresponding ScopeAxiom check Failed.",
