fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-124",
  description: "Proposal 030: Witness persistence — wire prove's discharged witnesses back so check can verify them across CLI invocations. Today prove produces a ProofWitness in-memory but discards it (let _witness = outcome.witness). check reads the source ProofRecord's witness field, which still carries the loader's placeholder TrustedAxiom('pending — not yet discharged'). For β.1's SmtDischarge replay to actually fire on user proofs, the witness must persist. Approach: sidecar JSON per project per rule QN under cache_root/projects/<repo>/witnesses/v1/<sanitised-qn>.json. Format: rule_qn, witness shape mirroring ProofWitness::SmtDischarge fields, state_hash, written_at. prove writes after each Discharged outcome; check reads the sidecar before falling back to source-witness — if a sidecar exists and its document_hash references a stored blob, the witness is used in place of the placeholder. Cleanly reverses on prove --refresh-cache (writes new sidecar, overwriting stale). Out of scope: in-source persistence (would need .anthill rewrites). Acceptance: cargo-test passes; new test verifies prove → check on a small fixture flips a Pending record from Trusted (placeholder) to Pass (verified).",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-04-28T12:55:20Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-125",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase β.3 — MetaCompose witness checking (KB-side). Per phase β.3 of docs/proposals/030-theorem-registry.md: per-meta-tactic structural validation. The contract for induction(over: T) is derived from <T-qn>.induction's registered principle (auto-registered in α.7); the kernel reads the principle's statement to determine the expected sub-witness shape. v0 scope: recurse on each sub-witness (using the same dispatch as top-level), pass when all pass. Per-meta-tactic shape contracts (induction needs base + step, ranking needs boundedness + decrease, etc.) deferred — that requires reading MetaTacticContract facts which the kernel doesn't yet have a schema for. The sidecar variant (in WI-124) already inlines the recursive replay logic; this WI lifts it to also fire for KB-term MetaCompose witnesses. Acceptance: cargo-test passes; an existing MetaCompose KB-term witness checks Pass when all sub-witnesses pass.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-04-28T13:57:11Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-126",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase β.6 — TrustedAxiom propagation through compound witness trees. Today's MetaCompose recursion short-circuits on the first non-Pass sub-witness, so a tree like [SmtDischarge_passes, TrustedAxiom_a, SmtDischarge_fails] would report Trusted (axiom_a) and never see the failure. Per phase β.6 of docs/proposals/030-theorem-registry.md: trust flag propagates through containing witnesses and is surfaced in CLI output, but failures must take precedence — the user needs to know if a discharge actually broke versus merely depending on trusted axioms. Change recursion to aggregate all sub-witness outcomes with priority Failed > Skipped > Trusted > Pass. A MetaCompose with all-Pass + N Trusted sub-witnesses reports Trusted with the combined reasons; same tree with one Failed reports Failed; mixed Failed + Trusted prefers Failed (trust still surfaces in the CLI summary). Apply to both KB-term recursion (check_meta_compose_witness) and sidecar recursion (check_witness_shape::MetaCompose). Acceptance: cargo-test passes; new test exercises the priority ordering — a MetaCompose [Pass, Trusted, Failed] reports Failed not Trusted.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-04-28T14:00:44Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-127",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase β.7 — tampering detection. Most of β.7's intent is already covered: α.5's content-addressed blobs detect blob tampering; β.1's verdict replay forces an attacker to forge a document Z3 accepts with the claimed verdict (Z3 is the trust base, documented in §β.1). What's left: an explicit test demonstrating that a manually-edited ProofRecord (witness-field swap, document_hash forgery) fails the check. Approach: (1) blob content hash already re-checked in check_smt_discharge_payload; (2) add a test storing a benign blob, recording a sidecar pointing at it with a CONTRADICTORY verdict label (Sat instead of Unsat), and verify check reports Failed. (3) document the tamper-resistance properties in a brief note. Acceptance: cargo-test passes; new test verifies that a sidecar+blob pair where the sidecar lies about the verdict fails verification.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-04-28T14:04:30Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-128",
  description: "Proposal 030 phase β.2 — SldDerivation real replay. DEFERRED: requires resolver instrumentation to capture a derivation tree. Today dispatch_derivation produces ProofWitness::SldDerivation { tree_hash: format!('sld-derivation:{rule_qn}') } as a placeholder; the kernel-check side has no real tree to replay. Scope when picked up: (1) extend resolve_kb / SearchStream to record a trace — list of (goal, rule_id, substitution) per derivation step; (2) serialize the trace as JSON; store as blob via cache::store_blob; tree_hash becomes real sha256 of the serialized trace; (3) at check time, load blob, for each recorded step verify rule_id still resolves to the same head term and substitution still unifies under current KB. The lf1 example doesn't use derivation-tactic proofs today, so β.2 has minimal user-visible payoff at v0. Pick up when a project actually relies on derivation discharges. Acceptance: cargo-test passes; new test verifies a small derivation proof can be checked.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
