  description: "Algebra abstraction: introduce Ring + VectorSpace specs in stdlib; have Float provide Ring, Vec3 provide VectorSpace[V = Vec3, F = Float]. Lifts the concrete vec_add / vec_sub / vec_scale / vec_zero operations from WI-137 into a proper algebraic typeclass, paralleling the existing Numeric spec pattern. Ring spec: add / sub / mul / zero / one + comm / assoc / identity / distributivity laws. VectorSpace[V, F] requires Ring[F]: vec_add / vec_sub / vec_scale / vec_zero + algebraic laws (currently in geometry.anthill). Acceptance: cargo-test passes; lf1 prove + check unchanged; new tests verify both specs load + the satisfaction declarations resolve.",
