fact Feedback(content: "Implemented. typing pass now collects errors as structured TypeError values via type_check_sorts_typed. New TypeError::Other variant + TypeErrorContext (EntityField/OperationReturn/OperationEffects/OperationMatch/Rule/Anonymous) carry Symbols for entity/field/op names instead of strings. TypeError::to_load_error(&kb) provides lossy back-compat for existing LoadError consumers; type_check_sorts wraps type_check_sorts_typed via that conversion. All 12 emission sites in typing.rs (check_value_against_*, check_entity_facts, check_operation_bodies, check_pattern_fragment, check_ho_apply_pattern, check_rule_typing) migrated. Public API unchanged for legacy callers. 4 new tests in tests/typing_test.rs::wi_019: structured field mismatch, return-type mismatch, span resolution, legacy LoadError compatibility.", at: "2026-05-03T20:04:35Z", workitem: "WI-019", author: "user")

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-172",
  description: "scaland mirror of WI-030 — SLD O(n²) optimization: lazy substitution in resolve/SearchStream.scala. stepChoicePoint had been eagerly walking every remaining goal applying the new substitution after each match: SearchStream.scala:191 (after a ground-fact match) and :206 (after a rule-body match). Fix: drop the eager applySubst-each from both paths; walk goals(0) lazily through frame.subst at goal-selection time in stepInit; memoize the walked form back into goals(0) so choice-point retries don't re-walk; skip the structural walk when σ is empty. Reduces O(n²) over the goal list to O(n × goal_size). Also fixed latent shape mismatch in Builtins.executeExtractSort surfaced by lazy walking — emit canonical nullary Fn shape (kb.makeNameTermFromSym) instead of Term.Ref(functor); pre-fix the eager apply silently overwrote the inconsistency. Added ResolveStats telemetry (steps, lazyWalkCalls), exposed via SearchStream.stats. Tests: smoke at n=50; acceptance asserts lazyWalkCalls < 8·n at n=400 and ratio < 6× between n=100 and n=400 (quadratic gives ~16×). Files: scaland/core/src/main/scala/anthill/{subst/Substitution,resolve/SearchStream,resolve/Builtins}.scala; scaland/core/src/test/scala/anthill/resolve/ResolveTest.scala (+2 tests + n-body fixture). Acceptance: sbt test green (122 tests).",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("scaland-sbt-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-05-04T05:11:52Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-171",
  description: "scaland — tighten bootstrap codegen + stand up anthill-scala-gen skeleton subproject (proposal 034 §anthill-scala-gen). Bootstrap path: (1) Laws.scala emission dropped from bootstrap entirely — rule term bodies are semantic, out of proposal 034 §Bootstrap's syntactic-only scope; the KB-driven anthill-scala-gen owns Laws emission. LawsGen.scala deleted. (2) build.sbt moved out of generate(pf) into a separate Bootstrap.buildSbt: GeneratedFile API; callers fold per-file generate() outputs into one tree and call buildSbt once — no per-file overwrite footgun. Tests: dropped vacuous Prop.passed placeholder + ill-shaped per-file build.sbt assertion; added (a) multi-file `???`-leak scan, (b) assertion that bootstrap does NOT emit Laws.scala, (c) multi-file regression asserting exactly one build.sbt in the merged tree. Skeleton: new sbt subproject scaland/anthill-scala-gen/ depending on scaland-core, with object Generator { def generate(kb: KnowledgeBase): IndexedSeq[GeneratedFile] = IndexedSeq.empty } and one smoke test. GeneratedFile is reused from anthill.codegen.scala (no duplicate type). Body of Generator deferred to a follow-up WI gated on a real consumer per proposal 034 §5. Acceptance: sbt test green (120 tests).",
